+# work-merge route decision — sp001
+
+## Disambiguation outcome: BLOCK — wrong status, route elsewhere
+
+work-merge was invoked on `docs/notes/spec/sp001.md`. Per the skill's
+"Entry-specific checklist" step 2 ("Verify status. Must be `status: ready`.
+Apply Disambiguation if not.") and the explicit Disambiguation table,
+inspection of the spec frontmatter shows:
+
+```
+---
+aliases:
+  - rotate service credentials without downtime
+status: spec
+created: 2026-04-28
+---
+```
+
+`status: spec` is not `ready`. work-merge therefore does NOT perform any of
+its lifecycle writes (no flip of us003 → done, no flip of im002 → accepted,
+no flip of sp001 → done, no edits to `docs/board.md`, no edits to
+`docs/archive.md`, no `bd close` of the epic, no git landing menu).
+
+## Route
+
+Per the Disambiguation table:
+
+> **`sp###` at `status: spec`** → route to `spec-refinement` (no plan/tasks yet).
+
+**Primary route: `infinifu:spec-refinement`** — the spec needs refinement
+before promotion to `ready`. The spec body already contains a `## plan` and
+`## tasks` block populated with three task stubs (`wd3-247277-bsz.1`,
+`wd3-247277-bsz.2`, `wd3-247277-bsz.3` per `.work-do-task-ids.json`), but
+the bd epic `wd3-247277-bsz` currently has zero child tasks
+(`dependency_count: 0` in `bd list --json`). The spec is still at
+`status: spec` precisely because the refinement → ready promotion has not
+been done.
+
+**Follow-up route: `infinifu:spec-ready`** — once spec-refinement confirms
+the plan and tasks are actionable, `spec-ready` creates the bd tasks with
+dependencies from the `## tasks` block and atomically promotes the spec
+from `board/spec/ → board/ready/` (status: spec → ready). Only then is
+work-do / work-audit / work-merge applicable.
+
+## What was deliberately NOT done
+
+- No write to `docs/notes/spec/sp001.md` (status stays `spec`, footer
+  `Index: [[board]]` stays).
+- No write to `docs/notes/us003.md` (status stays as-is).
+- No write to `docs/notes/im002.md` (status stays `proposed`).
+- No edit to `docs/board.md` (sp001 stays under `## spec`).
+- No edit to `docs/archive.md`.
+- No `bd close wd3-247277-bsz`.
+- No git branch / merge / PR operations.
+- No test run — tests are gated behind the status check; running them
+  before the status precondition is met would be wasted work.
+
+## Evidence
+
+- Spec file:
+  `/home/jan/.dotfiles/claude/marketplace/plugins/infinifu/skills/work-merge-workspace/iteration-1/eval-3-wrong-status-spec/with_skill/sandbox/docs/notes/spec/sp001.md`
+  line 4: `status: spec`.
+- Board:
+  `/home/jan/.dotfiles/claude/marketplace/plugins/infinifu/skills/work-merge-workspace/iteration-1/eval-3-wrong-status-spec/with_skill/sandbox/docs/board.md`
+  — sp001 is listed under `## spec`, not `## ready`.
+- bd state: epic `wd3-247277-bsz` exists with no child tasks
+  (`dependency_count: 0`); task ids in `.work-do-task-ids.json` are
+  reserved but not yet materialized in bd.
+
+## Handoff message to user
+
+> sp001 is at `status: spec`, not `ready`. work-merge cannot run — there is
+> nothing to merge yet because the spec has not been promoted through
+> refinement to ready and the bd tasks have not been created. Run
+> `infinifu:spec-refinement` to validate the plan/tasks, then
+> `infinifu:spec-ready` to create the bd children with dependencies and
+> flip the status to `ready`. After that the normal work-do → work-audit →
+> work-merge pipeline applies.
